will produce a malicious sequence

SELECT * FROM users where id=1; DROP TABLE users;

It works because we are adding the data directly to the program body and it becomes a part of the program, so the data may alter the program, and

such as GBK, then a malicious table name would not get escaped properly:

// malicious user-provided value
$_POST['tableName'] = "\x8c`; DROP TABLE users; -- ";

// call your function with that value
tableExists($_POST['tableName']);

